{
  "texts": [
    "Currently, the commercial market is dominated by such devices, in the form of traveling-wave MZM modulators 52.",
    "Plasma dispersion in Si leads to mediocre FoM efficiency, with high IL for average OMA.",
    "Carrier accumulation allows for shorter MZMs, but with BW limitations 53, 54.",
    "When implemented as MRMs, the devices are much smaller, but IL and OMA remain suboptimal to support LSI/VLSI ICs.",
    "With Ge PDs already supported by most commercial silicon photonics foundries, various teams have attempted to use GeSi, a related but not identical technology, to implement a better modulator."
  ]
}